sentence: Walter Davis Pidgeon (September 23, 1897 – September 25, 1984) was a Canadian-American actor.

While he was performing in amateur theatricals in Boston, Pidgeon was recommended to Elsie Janis, a prominent producer-actor-singer and impresario who was looking for a male singer for her revue.
She hired him and Pidgeon moved to New York City in 1923.

Discouraged with the quality of the roles he was getting, Pidgeon returned to New York in 1928 to resume his theater career.
